-- Step-by-step connection process\n1. Open Oracle SQL Developer.\n2. Click on the "Connections" pane.\n3. Click the green "+" icon to create a new connection.\n4. Enter the connection details:\n   - Connection Name: [YourConnectionName]\n   - Username: [YourUsername]\n   - Password: [YourPassword]\n   - Hostname: [YourOracleServerHost]\n   - Port: [YourOracleServerPort] (default is 1521)\n   - SID/Service Name: [YourDatabaseSIDorServiceName]\n5. Click "Test" to verify the connection.\n6. Click "Save" and "Connect".